JWT vs Session:
JWT (Token-based):
    Stored in client (browser/mobile)
    Sent in every request
    Authorization: Bearer <token>
Session-based: 
      Stored in server memory
      Client sends session ID (cookie)

      Feature	                  JWT	                      Session
      Storage	                  Client	                  Server
      Scalability	              High                  	  Low
      State	                    Stateless            	    Stateful
      Performance              	Faster (no DB lookup)    	Slower
      Security	                Needs care (token leak)	  Safer (server control)
