Stateless vs Stateful:
Stateless: Server stores nothing. Each request is independent
  Example:
      Request1 → complete  
      Request2 → independent  
      👉 Used with JWT
Stateful: Server stores session data  
  Example: Login → Session created → reused
      👉 Used with sessions
      Feature	      Stateless	          Stateful
      Memory	      No server storage	  Uses server memory
      Scaling      	Easy	              Hard
      Performance  	Better	            Limited
      Example	      JWT	                Session

